  "schemaVersion": "1.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "Cascadia CSZ source logic tree (Sypus & Wang, 2024)",
    "description": "First-draft encoding of Figure 4.1 from Sypus & Wang (2024), DOGAMI Open-File Report O-24-11, 'Improved Cascadia Earthquake Source Models for Tsunami Hazard Assessment' (USGS-NTHMP Cascadia Powell Center Tsunami Sources Working Group; refinements from H.K. Thio, 2024). Published branch weights are encoded as given. Splits the figure draws WITHOUT a weight use equal-weight PLACEHOLDERS so siblings sum to 1 (see metadata.placeholders) — these are NOT authoritative. The shared 'rupture-detail' subtree (Fig 4.1 p.26) is drawn once in the report and referenced from several parents; here it is defined once under DOGAMI > 'L' and stubbed elsewhere with marker leaves (value 'ref:rupture_detail') pending $ref subtree-reuse support.",
    "author": "Endor (draft from Sypus & Wang 2024)",
    "created": "2026-06-11",
    "tags": ["subduction", "cascadia", "powell-center", "draft", "sypus-wang-2024"],
    "source": "DOGAMI Open-File Report O-24-11, Figure 4.1 (pp. 25-27)",
    "placeholders": "Equal-weight placeholder splits (no weight published in Fig 4.1): Whole-margin/Partial; average-slip XL/L/M/SM; aleatory magnitude +1sigma/mean-median/-1sigma; Cluster-M8 event count 2/3/4/5; segmented segments B/C/Cprime/D/F; segment size Long/Medium/Short; along-strike Seaward/Landward vergence; splay geometry D/B; taper-to-trench 50/100%; rupture shape up/sym/down; termination depth tremor/locked/midpoint; event-slip 3-/5-asperity; asperity position.",
    "notes": "Recurrence values on the Floating branch are annual rates, not probabilities; they are carried in 'value' while the .25 epistemic weights are carried in 'weight'."
  },
